<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Jane Doe's Blog Post Writing Tip</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }
    .author-info {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .author-image {
      width: 100px;
      height: 100px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      margin-right: 20px;
    }
    .author-name {
      font-size: 24px;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .author-bio {
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .tip-title {
      font-size: 32px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .tip-content {
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .tip-tags {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    .tip-tag {
      padding: 5px 10px;
      background-color: #eee;
      border-radius: 5px;
      margin-right: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="author-info">
    <img class="author-image" src="https://example.com/jane-doe.jpg" alt="Jane Doe">
    <div class="author-name">Jane Doe</div>
    <div class="author-bio">Jane Doe is a software engineer and writer. She is passionate about helping people learn and grow.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="tip-title">How to Write a Good Blog Post</div>
  <div class="tip-content">
    <ol>
      <li>Choose a topic that you are passionate about and that you know something about.</li>
      <li>Do your research and make sure you have all the facts straight.</li>
      <li>Write in a clear and concise style.</li>
      <li>Proofread your work carefully before you publish it.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
  <div class="tip-tags">
    <div class="tip-tag">writing</div>
    <div class="tip-tag">blogging</div>
    <div class="tip-tag">content marketing</div>
  </div>

  <!-- Additional information not contained in the JSON instance -->
  <div class="additional-info">
    <h2>More Tips from Jane Doe</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Use strong keywords in your blog post title and throughout the content.</li>
      <li>Promote your blog post on social media and other online platforms.</li>
      <li>Respond to comments and questions from your readers.</li>
      <li>Keep your blog post updated with fresh content.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
